metadata.name: LONELY DIVER
metadata.description:
The eyes upon him, watchful, keen,
Every move, every word, is seen,
A conversation, a daunting task,
When every glance feels like a mask.

But though the fear may hold him back,
He takes a breath and tries to act,
For in the end, the truth is clear,
The ones who judge, they too hold fear.
